  "text": "The advanced stage at diagnosis in developing countries is contributed mainly to the lack of access to mammography, availability and quality of primary health care facilities, and the psychological and social impacts of treatments particularly for mastectomy. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] It is noteworthy that in 2003, a study conducted by the World Health Organization revealed that only 2.1% of Moroccan women aged 40 years or more had a clinical breast examination (or mammogram) in their life (Ministry of health, Morocco, 2007) .",
